GURPS Space has a world generation system that is probably more
"realistic" than that of Traveller and certainly more detailed if you
do the full generation instead of the basic (fleshing out the whole
system and including world details like axial tilt, orbit times, day
length and frequency of earthquakes).   And you generate much higher
gravity world than the maximum in Traveller, although they're rare
when randomly generated.  It also has a really nifty random alien
generator, animals and people.  Between the two of them, they dominate
the book.  I can't say whether that would be worth it for you.
